{
  "text": "Although \u03b2 3 -adrenoceptors are known to be abundant in the detrusor smooth muscle and play a key role in relaxation of the human urinary bladder via the activation of adenylate cyclase during urine storage, little is known about the expression of \u03b2-adrenoceptor subtypes in the human urinary bladder urothelium. Harmon and colleagues (2005) identified the presence of \u03b2-adrenoceptors on immortalized human urothelial cell membranes but not the specific subtype involved. To our knowledge, the present study is the first to report the presence of \u03b2 1 -, \u03b2 2 -, and \u03b2 3 -adrenoceptors in human urinary bladder urothelium by RT-PCR and immunohistochemistry. While previous reports have demonstrated the distribution of mucosal \u03b2 3 -adrenoceptor mRNA in human small intestine, stomach, and colon using RT-PCR and immunohistochemical techniques [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , their functional role in this mucosa remains to be elucidated.",
